Admiral Linda L. Fagan has been confirmed by the Senate as the Commandant of the U.S. Coast Guard, making her the first woman to hold the rank of four-star admiral in the Coast Guard and the first woman Service Chief of any U.S. military service. Her leadership, experience, and integrity are highly regarded, and she is expected to advance the Coast Guard's mission of ensuring maritime safety and security. This confirmation sends a powerful message to women and girls across the nation that they have a place in protecting their country at the highest level. The administration is committed to promoting more qualified women in senior leadership and command roles in the military.